---
import { site } from '../config/site';
---

  <section class="section appear" id="quickstart">
    <div class="section-head">
      <span class="no">04</span>
      <h2>Quickstart, two paths.</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="qstart">
      <div>
        <h3>New repo · <em>init</em></h3>
        <p>Install the runtime, then bootstrap the harness. For app-shaped repos, add the Rust + React scaffold preset.</p>
<pre><span class="c"># from anywhere</span>
<span class="h">cargo install</span> jig-sh

<span class="c"># or build from source</span>
<span class="h">git clone</span> {site.repoCloneUrl}
<span class="h">cd</span> jig-sh &amp;&amp; <span class="h">cargo install</span> --path crates/jig

<span class="c"># harness-only repo</span>
<span class="h">jig init</span> /path/to/target-repo \
  --repo-name target-repo \
  --sqlx-enabled <span class="a">false</span>

<span class="c"># greenfield app scaffold</span>
<span class="h">jig init</span> /path/to/target-repo \
  --preset <span class="a">rust-react</span> \
  --db <span class="a">postgres</span> \
  --frontends web,landing,admin</pre>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3>Existing repo · <em>adopt</em></h3>
        <p>Preview first, then apply with <code>--write</code>. Existing Makefiles and app code stay project-owned.</p>
<pre><span class="c"># inside the repo</span>
<span class="h">jig adopt</span> .
<span class="h">jig adopt</span> . --write

<span class="c"># later, pull in template updates</span>
<span class="h">jig update</span>
<span class="h">jig update</span> --recopy   <span class="c"># full re-render</span>
<span class="h">jig update</span> --force    <span class="c"># overwrite managed</span></pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
